# Photo Booth OS ‚Äî Manual Setup Guide

Complete this guide **before** opening the dashboard or importing n8n workflows.
Estimated time: 90‚Äì120 minutes.

---

## Prerequisites

```bash
cd photobooth-os
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env and fill ALL values (especially generate secrets with openssl rand -hex 32)
docker compose up -d
bash scripts/init-databases.sh
bash scripts/healthcheck.sh
```

All services should show ‚úÖ before proceeding.

---

## SECTION A ‚Äî Twenty CRM Custom Fields

Open https://crm.photobooth.local ‚Üí Sign up with your admin email.

Navigate: **Settings ‚Üí Data Model ‚Üí People**

For each field below, click **Add Field** and configure exactly:

| # | Field Name | Type | Options / Notes |
|---|-----------|------|-----------------|
| 1 | `eventDate` | Date | ‚Äî |
| 2 | `eventType` | Select | Birthday, Corporate, Wedding, School, Other |
| 3 | `eventAddress` | Text | ‚Äî |
| 4 | `guestCount` | Number | ‚Äî |
| 5 | `inquiryStatus` | Select | Follow Up, Unsure, Denied, Booked |
| 6 | `depositPaid` | Boolean | ‚Äî |
| 7 | `depositAmount` | Currency | ‚Äî |
| 8 | `contractSent` | Boolean | ‚Äî |
| 9 | `contractSigned` | Boolean | ‚Äî |
| 10 | `invoiceNinjaClientId` | Text | ‚Äî |
| 11 | `invoiceNinjaQuoteId` | Text | ‚Äî |
| 12 | `docusealContractId` | Text | ‚Äî |
| 13 | `calendarEventId` | Text | ‚Äî |
| 14 | `source` | Select | Website Form, Manual Entry, Referral, Walk-In |
| 15 | `travelMiles` | Number | ‚Äî |
| 16 | `estimatedCost` | Currency | ‚Äî |
| 17 | `estimatedRevenue` | Currency | ‚Äî |
| 18 | `estimatedMargin` | Currency | ‚Äî |
| 19 | `notes` | Long Text | ‚Äî |

After all 19 fields are added:
1. Go to **Settings ‚Üí API Keys**
2. Click **Create API Key**, name it "Dashboard"
3. Copy the key ‚Üí paste into `dashboard/js/config.js` as `TWENTY_API_KEY`

**Verification:**
```bash
curl -X POST https://crm.photobooth.local/api \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"query":"query { findManyPeople { edges { node { id } } } }"}'
```
Should return JSON with `data.findManyPeople.edges` array (possibly empty).

